name: UBS BBG MSCI US Liquid Corp Sustainable UCITS ETF USD acc
description_en: The UBS BBG MSCI US Liquid Corp Sustainable UCITS ETF USD acc seeks to track the Bloomberg MSCI US Liquid Corporates Sustainable index. The Bloomberg MSCI US Liquid Corporates Sustainable index tracks the most liquid ESG (environmental, social and governance) screened, USD denominated bonds issued by US companies. All maturities are included. Rating: Investment Grade. The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.13% p.a.. The UBS BBG MSCI US Liquid Corp Sustainable UCITS ETF USD acc is the only ETF that tracks the Bloomberg MSCI US Liquid Corporates Sustainable index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by sampling technique (buying a selection of the most relevant index constituents). The interest income (coupons) in the ETF is accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. The UBS BBG MSCI US Liquid Corp Sustainable UCITS ETF USD acc is a small ETF with 24m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 30 August 2019 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less

name: Xtrackers DAX ESG Screened UCITS ETF 2C USD Hedged
description_en: The Xtrackers DAX ESG Screened UCITS ETF 2C USD Hedged seeks to track the DAX® ESG Screened (USD Hedged) index. The DAX® ESG Screened (USD Hedged) index tracks the largest, most liquid German stocks while taking into account ESG exclusion filters (environmental, social and corporate governance). Companies involved in weapons, armaments, tobacco, thermal coal, oil sands or nuclear power and companies that violate the principles of the United Nations Global Compact are excluded. The parent index is the DAX®. Excluded companies are not replaced. The maximum weight of a company is capped at 10%. Currency hedged to US-Dollar (USD). The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.19% p.a.. The Xtrackers DAX ESG Screened UCITS ETF 2C USD Hedged is the only ETF that tracks the DAX® ESG Screened (USD Hedged) index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The dividends in the ETF are accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. The Xtrackers DAX ESG Screened UCITS ETF 2C USD Hedged is a very small ETF with 10m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 13 January 2016 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less

name: UBS MSCI Japan Socially Responsible UCITS ETF JPY dis
description_en: The UBS MSCI Japan Socially Responsible UCITS ETF JPY dis seeks to track the MSCI Japan SRI Low Carbon Select 5% Issuer Capped index. The MSCI Japan SRI Low Carbon Select 5% Issuer Capped index tracks Japanese stocks considering only companies with very high Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) ratings relative to their sector peers, to ensure the inclusion of the best of class companies from an ESG perspective. The weight of each company is capped to 5%. The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.19% p.a.. The UBS MSCI Japan Socially Responsible UCITS ETF JPY dis is the only ETF that tracks the MSCI Japan SRI Low Carbon Select 5% Issuer Capped index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The dividends in the ETF are distributed to the investors (Semi annually). The UBS MSCI Japan Socially Responsible UCITS ETF JPY dis has 341m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 22 July 2015 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less

name: Amundi USD Fed Funds Rate UCITS ETF Acc
description_en: The Amundi USD Fed Funds Rate UCITS ETF Acc seeks to track the Solactive Fed Funds Effective Rate index. The Solactive Fed Funds Effective Rate index tracks a daily rolling exposure to the Federal Funds Effective Rate, the benchmark short-term money market interest rate in the US. The Federal Funds Rate is set at meetings of the Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC). The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.10% p.a.. The Amundi USD Fed Funds Rate UCITS ETF Acc is the cheapest and largest ETF that tracks the Solactive Fed Funds Effective Rate index. The MSCI Emerging SRI S-Series PAB 5% Capped index tracks equity market performance of emerging markets considering only companies with very high Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) ratings relative to their sector peers, to ensure the inclusion of the best of class companies from an ESG perspective. Companies that generate significant portions of their revenues in non-sustainable activities are excluded. In addition, companies involved in the following industries are excluded: Coal mining for power generation, conventional and alternative oil/gas extraction, power generation from fossil fuel and nuclear energy. The weight of each company is capped to 5%. The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.31% p.a.. The BNP Paribas Easy MSCI Emerging SRI S-Series PAB 5% Capped UCITS ETF USD Acc is the cheapest ETF that tracks the MSCI Emerging SRI S-Series PAB 5% Capped index. The ETF was launched on 21 July 2016 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less

The Bloomberg Emerging Markets USD Sovereign & Agency 3% Country Capped (EUR Hedged) index tracks the US dollar-denominated debt issued by sovereign and agency EM issuers. Corporate issues are not eligible. Country weights are capped at 3% of total amount outstanding of all eligible issues. Currency hedged to Euro (EUR). The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.28% p.a.. The UBS BBG USD EM Sovereign UCITS ETF hEUR acc is the only ETF that tracks the Bloomberg Emerging Markets USD Sovereign & Agency 3% Country Capped (EUR Hedged) index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by sampling technique (buying a selection of the most relevant index constituents). The interest income (coupons) in the ETF is accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. The UBS BBG USD EM Sovereign UCITS ETF hEUR acc has 222m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 29 April 2016 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less

name: UBS BBG USD EM Sovereign UCITS ETF hGBP dis
description_en: The UBS BBG USD EM Sovereign UCITS ETF hGBP dis seeks to track the Bloomberg Emerging Markets USD Sovereign & Agency 3% Country Capped (GBP Hedged) index. The Bloomberg Emerging Markets USD Sovereign & Agency 3% Country Capped (GBP Hedged) index tracks the US dollar-denominated debt issued by sovereign and agency EM issuers. Corporate issues are not eligible. Country weights are capped at 3% of total amount outstanding of all eligible issues. Currency hedged to British Pound (GBP). The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.28% p.a.. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by sampling technique (buying a selection of the most relevant index constituents). The interest income (coupons) in the ETF is distributed to the investors (Semi annually). The UBS BBG USD EM Sovereign UCITS ETF hGBP dis is a small ETF with 84m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 29 April 2016 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less
